`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `applyTierUpgrade` takes `baseEffectPower` (the basic tier's original value from `tools.json`) and multiplies by the absolute effectMultiplier. This avoids drift when chaining upgrades — you always compute from the pristine base, not from a previously-multiplied value. The caller stores the base, the forging system just applies math.
