`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `SmeltStatus` union deliberately omits `"failed"` — unlike cooking where a campfire going out mid-cook fails the slot, forge smelting is always uninterruptible once started. Simpler state machines are easier to reason about and test. Don't add states you don't need yet.
